"I would like to address a few comments from the PR that I opened. THe first one is ```DiscoverAndRegister has no test coverage. The test file tests New, Wrap, and agent methods, but none of the PATH-scanning and registration logic — including deduplication, name-conflict detection, and non-executable file skipping. Given the tested behaviors in this file and the codebase's comprehensive testing conventions, tests for DiscoverAndRegister should be added.```\n\n---\n\nAnother comment: ```The stderr output from the subprocess is not trimmed before being embedded in the error message. Shells and many CLI tools terminate their stderr output with a trailing newline, which causes the error message to contain a trailing newline when wrapped in fmt.Errorf. Other places in the codebase that build errors from command output consistently use strings.TrimSpace (for example, gitops/diff.go:51, git_operations.go:297). The errMsg should be trimmed: strings.TrimSpace(stderrBuf.String()).```\n\n---\n\nAnother one: ```The reference implementation is missing the get-session-id subcommand, which is listed as \"Always Required\" in the protocol documentation. When the CLI calls GetSessionID(), the binary will print \"unknown subcommand: get-session-id\" to stderr and exit with code 1. The function defined in external.go will silently return empty string on error, but this is still a gap between the protocol spec and the reference implementation.```"